The paper proposes a novel algorithm for network representation using cross-domain random walks. This involves transferring knowledge from a structural rich domain to a structural scarce domain. The paper focuses on machine learning tasks and employs unsupervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
